    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><date>Monday</date> Evening <date>June 16/56</date></p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Again I trouble<lb/> you with “an effusion” drawn<lb/> from me by
                your holding<lb/> me up to the notice of the<lb/> orthodox in a bright light<lb/>
                reflecting on our most<lb/> venerable sages of blessed<lb/> memory. I hope you<lb/>
                will be able to publish<lb/> it in the Occident for <date>July</date><lb/> as I am
                anxious to <hi rend="underline">right</hi><lb/> myself before the learned<lb/> and
                discriminating <hi rend="underline">readers</hi><lb/> (including all the “Lions”
                of<lb/> the age) of “The Occident”!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The article involves a grave<lb/> and momentous question<lb/> viz
                the Rabbinical authority)</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I trust the day will yet come<lb/> when the chaff shall be<lb/> separated from the
                wheat<lb/> and the latter alone preserved!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Now for the latest news!<lb/> Last <date>Shabat</date> the
                officiating<lb/> Parnass <persName>Saml Lazarus Esq</persName> felt<lb/> it his duty
                to send the<lb/> Shamas to <hi rend="underline">four</hi> young men<lb/> who were
                devoutly——<lb/>talking, <persName>Messrs Edmund H.</persName><lb/>
                <persName>Harman<add>?</add></persName>
                <persName>Joshual H.</persName> &amp;<lb/>
                <persName>Mortimer H.</persName> You can<lb/> imagine their indignation<lb/> upon
                the public reprimand<lb/> which they evinced by loud<lb/> words after school in
                the<lb/> vestibule. They viewed<lb/> the affair as an <hi rend="underline"
                    >expression</hi> of<lb/> personal spite on the part<lb/> of the vice
                President!</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>alleging that many others<lb/> older and wiser are allowed<lb/> to converse with
                impunity<lb/> while they were made <hi rend="underline">victims</hi><lb/> to
                personal and family hatred.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">One thing I do know and<lb/> can attest to, many behave<lb/>
                shamefully with perfect<lb/> impunity. Not that I approve<lb/> or justify indecorum
                in<lb/> a place that <hi rend="underline">should be</hi><lb/> considered sacred.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You are probably aware<lb/> to day two trustees were<lb/> elected,
                in place of <persName>Messrs<lb/> B Nathan</persName> &amp; <persName>Simn
                        Graham<add>?</add></persName><lb/> the candidates were <persName>Messrs<lb/>
                    Joe Soria</persName> and <persName>B. I. Hart</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I will endeavor to add<lb/> in a P. S. the result.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The weather is <hi rend="underline">getting</hi></p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>delightfully warm, and this is<lb/> enough on this very interesting<lb/> topic!
                    <persName>Mr Jeffn. Moise</persName><lb/> has been here some days<lb/> is
                thought very intelligent<lb/> and loquacious, and by some<lb/> who probably do not
                understand<lb/> English, pedantic!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With remembrance to my<lb/> relatives, I am dr sir yours<lb/> very
                Respectfully and sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">M Solomons</persName>
            </p>
            <p><date>Tuesday</date> Morning =<lb/> Please ask <persName>Aunt M's</persName><lb/>
                letter recd to day —<lb/>
                <persName>Messrs Soria</persName> &amp; <persName>Hart</persName><lb/> elected by a
                large<lb/> majority!!!</p>
        </body>
